    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but i've been reading some stuff online saying that originalism is basically just a way for conservative judges to push their own political agenda under the guise of law. how would a scholar respond to that criticism? like, is there any truth to the idea that it's just a tool for partisan outcomes?",
